<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-14957] Default value for state.dir is confusing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14957</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default value for state.dir is documented as /var/folders/0t/68svdzmx1sld0mxjl8dgmmzm0000gq/T//kafka-streams&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is misleading, the value will be different in each environment as it computed using System.getProperty(&quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot;). We should update the description to mention how the path is computed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
